The article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Donald Trump on March 6, 2017. The memorandum discusses the implementation of immediate heightened screening and vetting protocols for visas and other immigration benefits, ensuring the enforcement of all laws for entry into the United States, and increasing transparency among departments and agencies of the federal government. The policy aims to keep American citizens safe from terrorist attacks and prevent the entry of foreign nationals who may aid or commit violent, criminal, or terrorist acts. The Secretary of State and the Secretary of Homeland Security, in consultation with the Attorney General, are directed to implement protocols and procedures that enhance the screening and vetting of applications for visas and immigration benefits. Additionally, the memorandum emphasizes the enforcement of all existing grounds of inadmissibility and subsequent compliance with related laws after admission. The Secretaries of State and Homeland Security are also required to issue regular reports regarding visas and adjustments of immigration status to provide more information to the American public. The memorandum concludes with general provisions and authorizes the Secretary of State to publish it in the Federal Register.